\section dal_compile_link Compile and link against the DAL

The minimum include statement to be put into your code if you want to use 
functionality of the DAL from a C++ program is:
\code
#include <dal/dal.h>
\endcode

\section dal_python_interface Python interface

Typical python usage of the <b><i>pydal</i></b> module might look like this:

<ol>
  <li>Working with a MeasurementSet:
  \code
  import sys
  import pydal as dal
  from pylab import *

  msds= dal.dalDataset()
  if ( msds.open(sys.argv[1]) ):
	sys.exit(1)

  tablename = "MAIN";

  msds.setFilter("UVW")
  title("UV coverage for\n" + sys.argv[1] )

  maintable = msds.openTable( tablename )

  # get the UVW column
  uvw_column = maintable.getColumn("UVW")

  # get the data from the column
  data = uvw_column.data()

  # plot the data
  xlabel("U(-U)")
  ylabel("V(-V)")
  plot(data[0],data[1],'r,',-(data[0]),-(data[1]),'b,')
  show()
  \endcode
</ol>

